e as forms of labor. This collection does just that, bringing together the usually disparate fields of military and labor history. The contributors—including Robert Johnson, Frank Tallett, and Gilles Veinstein—undertake the first systematic comparative analysis of military labor across Europe, Africa, America, the Middle East, and Asia. In doing so, they explore the circumstances that have produced starkly different systems of recruiting and employing soldiers in different parts of the globe over the last five hundred years.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh1 aAksan, Virginia H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAmersfoort, Herman, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBailey, Beth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeşikçi, Mehmet, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHippler, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaya, S. Yelda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKolff, Dirk H.A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeonhard, Jörn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMiller, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoll-Murata, Christine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRobinson, David M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRovinello, Marco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRoy, Kaushik, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSikora, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/v